The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Das GM title official now

New Delhi: Neelotpal Das was officially declared the 13th Grandmaster of India by Fide, the world governing body, while wonder kid Parimarjan Negi became the countrys youngest-ever International Master on Saturday. 

Himanshu Sharma of Haryana was also awarded the IM title at Fides conference held on the sidelines of the Chess Olympiad in Turin, Italy. 

However, Deepan Chakravarthy, who also secured his third GM norm at the recently concluded National A Championships in Hyderabad, would be referred to the Fide technical committee as the Tamil Nadu player is still to attain the required Elo rating points for the title. 

 (PTI) 




